main event: On June 30, 1966, a metallic object was observed landing in a field near Presque Isle, Pennsylvania.
interesting points: The object was about 30 feet in diameter and 8 feet high, described as metallic silver with a domed top., The object descended slowly and hovered before landing, illuminating the area with a bright white light., After a few minutes, the light went out and the object ascended rapidly, disappearing from sight., Investigators found impressions approximately 18 inches in diameter at the alleged landing site., Despite military and law enforcement involvement, no physical evidence was found, and the case remains unresolved.
sighted object: metallic object approximately 30 feet in diameter
witness description: There are no specific descriptions of witnesses in the report.
